<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
  	<h2>Float Classes</h2>
  	<p>Change the float behavior of an element by adding <code>.u-floatLeft</code> or <code>.u-floatRight</code> to an HTML element. To clear floats, add the class <code>.u-clearfix</code> to the parent element.</p> 
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
  	<h2>Clearfix</h2>
  	<p>The <code>.u-clearfix</code> class clears floated elements as a parent or child.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
   <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h2>Equal Heights</h2>
    <p>In order to achieve equal height areas, we wrap a <code>div.u-equalHeight</code> in between the row and columns. The columns will all have equal heights.</p>
    <p>We can also achieve equal heights with block grids, by adding a class of <code>.u-equalHeight</code> to the block grid's <code>ul</code>.</p>
   </div>
</div>


<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h2>Text Align</h2>
    <p>Use the <code>.u-textAlignLeft</code> or <code>.u-textAlignCenter</code> or <code>.u-textAlignRight</code> to align the text within it's parent accordingly. Apply the class to the parent to avoid repeating the utility unnecessarily.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
   <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h2>Capitalization</h2>
    <p>In order to achieve capitalized text, we add a class of <code>.u-capitalize</code> to any element.</p>
   </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
   <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h2>Vertically Center Back Links</h2>
    <p>To vertically center text in a parent,  <code>.u-centerVertical</code> to any element contained within a header with an <code>h1</code>.</p>
   </div>
</div>